What is devops ?
DevOps is a software development approach that emphasizes collaboration between development and operations teams to streamline the delivery of high-quality software through automation and continuous integration.

Why devops?
In simple terms, DevOps is important because it helps organizations deliver software faster, more reliably, and with higher quality.
It achieves this by breaking down barriers between development and operations teams, fostering collaboration, and automating processes.
This approach enables quicker and more frequent releases, reduces the risk of errors, and enhances overall efficiency, ultimately leading to better customer satisfaction and business outcomes.

